## Public / Open Group

Great for projects, knowledge sharing or common interest\.

Any employee in your Network can see conversations in a Public Group\.

ENGAGEMENT TIP:

Use PUBLIC GROUPS as the default\. Create a Private Group only when necessary\.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

## Private/Closed Group

Only employees who have been added as Members can see conversations in a Private Group\.

Good for communication within smaller teams\.

COLLABORATION TIP:

If your team starts out in a Private Group, discuss switching to a Public Group every few months\.

![](data:image/png;base64,)
